  "base_commit": "b4bc3aa19edf988c6bedb5e964325f316f26671e",
  "pr_number": 1930,
  "issue_number": 1929,
  "issue_title": "[Bug]: \"as though it didn't have hexproof\" (Detection Tower class) does nothing \u2014 `StaticMode::IgnoreHexproof` is never produced by the parser and never enforced by targeting (CR 702.11e)",
  "issue_body": "## Summary\n\nEffects that let a player target hexproof permanents **\"as though they didn't have hexproof\"** \u2014 the primary answers to hexproof commanders \u2014 have no effect. `StaticMode::IgnoreHexproof` exists and is registered, and `can_target` even carries a comment claiming \"*CR 702.11e: IgnoreHexproof bypasses this*\", but:\n\n1. **Targeting never checks it.** `can_target` consults the `Shroud` / `Hexproof` / `HexproofFrom` keywords and protection \u2014 but there is no `IgnoreHexproof` check anywhere. The comment is aspirational; the code does not implement it.\n2. **The parser never produces it.** No code in `crates/engine/src/parser` emits `StaticMode::IgnoreHexproof`; the Oracle phrase \"as though it/they didn't have hexproof\" isn't recognized, so even the parse is missing.\n\n`IgnoreHexproof` is a doubly-dead static: a defined, registered, `Display`/`FromStr`-round-tripping variant that nothing creates and nothing reads. As a result, **Detection Tower** and similar hexproof-bypass effects are inert \u2014 a hexproof creature remains an illegal target even after the controller activates the bypass.\n\n## Cards (a played, high-impact class)\n\n- **Detection Tower** \u2014 \"{1}, {T}: Until end of turn, your opponents and creatures they control with hexproof can be the targets of spells and abilities you control **as though they didn't have hexproof**.\" A Commander staple \u2014 one of the few colorless answers to hexproof generals.\n- Other \"target \u2026 as though it didn't have hexproof\" effects in the same class.\n- **Related dead static (same hexproof-answer area):** `StaticMode::CantHaveKeyword` is likewise never consumed in `crates/engine/src/game`, so the \"**can't have or be granted hexproof or shroud**\" half of **Arcane Lighthouse** is also unimplemented. (Arcane Lighthouse's \"lose hexproof and shroud\" half works via `RemoveKeyword`; the \"can't have/be granted\" half does not.)\n\n## Expected\n\nWhile the bypass effect is active, the controller's spells and abilities may target the named hexproof permanents (CR 702.11e \u2014 an effect may allow targeting \"as though\" the permanent didn't have hexproof). Other players' spells/abilities are unaffected.\n\n## Actual\n\nThe bypass clause is dropped at parse time, and `can_target` continues to treat the permanent as hexproof. The hexproof permanent stays an illegal target for everyone, so Detection Tower does nothing.\n\n## Root cause\n\n### 1. `can_target` never checks `IgnoreHexproof`\n\n`crates/engine/src/game/targeting.rs:1322-1356` \u2014 `can_target` returns `false` for `Hexproof` (when `obj.controller != source_controller`) and `HexproofFrom`, with a comment at line 1338 referencing `IgnoreHexproof` \u2014 but no code path consults it. A whole-crate search finds `StaticMode::IgnoreHexproof` only in: the enum definition, the registry insert (`handle_rule_mod`, inert), that lone comment, and a `Display`/`FromStr` round-trip test. It is never compared or queried for targeting.\n\n### 2. The parser never produces it\n\nA search of `crates/engine/src/parser` for `IgnoreHexproof` / \"didn't have hexproof\" / \"as though \u2026 hexproof\" returns nothing. Detection Tower's bypass clause has no parser branch, so no `IgnoreHexproof` effect is created.\n\n## CR reference (verified against `docs/MagicCompRules.txt`)\n\n- **CR 702.11a** \u2014 Hexproof: a permanent with hexproof can't be the target of spells or abilities an opponent controls.\n- **CR 702.11e** \u2014 an effect may allow a player to target a hexproof permanent \"as though it didn't have hexproof\" (the bypass `IgnoreHexproof` models).\n\n## Proposed fix shape (build for the class)\n\n`can_target` already receives `source_controller`, and the engine already supports player-scoped statics via `player_has_static_other(state, player_id, name)` / `check_static_ability` \u2014 so enforcement is tractable **without** threading new source context (unlike spell-vs-ability targeting).\n\n1. **Parser** (`crates/engine/src/parser/oracle_effect/`) \u2014 recognize \"[opponents'/target] hexproof permanents can be the targets of spells and abilities you control as though they didn't have hexproof\" as an until-end-of-turn effect that grants the controller `IgnoreHexproof` (a player-scoped continuous effect). Compose with nom combinators; the affected scope (\"creatures your opponents control\", etc.) rides on the existing filter machinery.\n2. **`crates/engine/src/game/targeting.rs`** \u2014 in `can_target`, before returning `false` for `Hexproof` / `HexproofFrom`, check whether `source_controller` has an active `IgnoreHexproof` effect; if so, skip the hexproof restrictions (CR 702.11e). Shroud is intentionally unaffected (Detection Tower ignores hexproof only).\n3. **(Optional, same area)** wire `CantHaveKeyword` into the layer system so \"can't have or be granted [keyword]\" suppresses `AddKeyword` grants of the named keyword \u2014 completing Arcane Lighthouse.\n4. **Tests** \u2014 a hexproof opponent creature is an illegal target normally, but a legal target for the controller's spell once `IgnoreHexproof` is active; an opponent's spell still can't target it; the bypass expires at end of turn.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- [ ] \"as though it/they didn't have hexproof\" grants the controller an `IgnoreHexproof` effect for its stated duration.\n- [ ] While active, the controller's spells/abilities may target the named hexproof permanents; other players' may not.\n- [ ] `IgnoreHexproof` is actually consulted in `can_target` (the existing comment becomes true).\n- [ ] Shroud is unaffected by `IgnoreHexproof`; no regression to `Hexproof` / `HexproofFrom` for sources without the bypass.\n- [ ] Target-legality + parser building-block tests; `./scripts/check-parser-combinators.sh` and `cargo clippy -D warnings` clean.\n- [ ] CR 702.11e annotation verified.\n\n## References\n\n- `crates/engine/src/game/targeting.rs:1322-1356` \u2014 `can_target` (checks Hexproof/HexproofFrom; the `IgnoreHexproof` comment at :1338 is never implemented).\n- `crates/engine/src/game/static_abilities.rs:95` \u2014 `IgnoreHexproof` registry insert (`handle_rule_mod`, inert; the only game-side reference).\n- `crates/engine/src/game/static_abilities.rs:1075` \u2014 `player_has_static_other` (the player-scoped query the fix can use with `source_controller`).\n- `crates/engine/src/types/statics.rs:616` \u2014 `StaticMode::IgnoreHexproof` definition.\n- Related dead static: `StaticMode::CantHaveKeyword` \u2014 no consumption in `crates/engine/src/game` (Arcane Lighthouse \"can't have/be granted hexproof or shroud\").",
  "merged_at": "2026-06-03T00:08:16.000Z",
